sentences: Pandit Parameshwar Hegde (born 6 May 1956) is an Indian Hindustani classical vocalist.
In 1976 that Parameshwar Hegde went to Dharwad to seek advanced training under Pandith Basavaraj Rajguru.
Over a decade and a half, he taught Parameshwar Hegde the best compositions from his repertoire.
Now a resident of Bangalore, he is a major attraction at music festivals all over India and has also traveled on concert tours abroad, to the U.S.A, Canada, United Kingdom and the Gulf countries.
Many awards have adorned his musical legacy including the prestigious Karnataka State Award (Rajyotsava Award) for the year 2005 for his contribution to the field of music.
Recently he has been bestowed with Kalaashri award by Karanataka Sangeetha-Nritya academy for the year of 2016.
